  "prompt": "Which songs are best for shrilled voice?",
  "response": "If you have a shrilled or high-pitched voice, you might want to look for songs that complement your vocal qualities and allow you to showcase your range and pitch. Here are some suggestions:\n\n1. **Pop Songs:**\n   - \u201cChandelier\u201d by Sia\n   - \u201cAll About That Bass\u201d by Meghan Trainor\n   - \u201cLove on Top\u201d by Beyonc\u00e9\n   - \u201cRoyals\u201d by Lorde\n   - \u201cShake It Off\u201d by Taylor Swift\n\n2. **Rock and Alternative Songs:**\n   - \u201cLivin' on a Prayer\u201d by Bon Jovi\n   - \u201cRolling in the Deep\u201d by Adele\n   - \u201cSweet Child O\u2019 Mine\u201d by Guns N\u2019 Roses\n   - \u201cBohemian Rhapsody\u201d by Queen\n\n3. **Musical Theatre:**\n   - \u201cDefying Gravity\u201d from \"Wicked\"\n   - \u201cThink of Me\u201d from \"The Phantom of the Opera\"\n   - \u201cOn My Own\u201d from \"Les Mis\u00e9rables\"\n   - \u201cAnd I Am Telling You I'm Not Going\u201d from \"Dreamgirls\"\n\n4. **Classical/Opera:**\n   - \u201cQueen of the Night Aria\u201d from Mozart's \"The Magic Flute\"\n   - \u201cO mio babbino caro\u201d by Puccini\n   - \u201cCasta Diva\u201d from Bellini's \"Norma\"\n\n5. **Other Genres:**\n   - \u201cDog Days Are Over\u201d by Florence + The Machine\n   - \u201cA Natural Woman\u201d by Aretha Franklin\n   - \u201cHalo\u201d by Beyonc\u00e9\n\nThese songs have notable high notes and strong vocal parts that can be suitable for those with shrilled or higher-pitched voices. Remember, it's important to pick songs that you feel comfortable singing and that fit your vocal style and range.",
